#NOTE  Actual size of box is in the image below
TEXT(beginproblem());
BEGIN_TEXT
The line graph below shows the height of the water in a water tank as it fills.$BR The numbers representing the heights of the water are missing.  
$BR

\{ image( insertGraph($graph), tex_size=>$TEXSIZE,
    height=>$HEIGHT, width=>$WIDTH
    ) \}
$BR 
The height of the water in the tank increases at a rate of 4 inches per minute $BR
as the tank fills.  $PAR
The 3 missing numbers (in increasing order) are \{ans_rule(1 )\},\{ans_rule(1 )\}, and \{ans_rule(1 )\}.
END_TEXT
ANS(Real(20)->cmp);
ANS(Real(40)->cmp);
ANS(Real(60)->cmp);
BEGIN_SOLUTION
$PAR Solution $PAR
The tank starts out empty since the graph begins at time 0.  If the height 
increases at 4 inches$BR per minutes, it increases by 20 inches in the fiirst
five minutes  and so, at time 5 minutes it has$BR height 20.  It then increases by another 20 inches  in each of the following 5 minute intervals,$BR reaching 40 inches at time ten minutes and 60 inches at time 15 minutes.
END_SOLUTION

;
